“Go for the jugular!” That was the message from new Cape Town City coach Benni McCarthy to his players on his first day in the job. McCarthy was unveiled on Tuesday as the new head coach of City, replacing Eric Tinkler, who has joined SuperSport United after just a single season in Cape Town. This is 39-year-old McCarthy’s first post in charge, but he wants his team to go even higher than last season, where they ended third in the Premiership and won the Telkom Knockout. Hear what McCarthy said about the type of approach he hopes to instil at his new team… To view this video please enable JavaScript, and consider upgrading to a web browser that
    supports HTML5 video This is a modal window. Beginning of dialog window. Escape will cancel and close the window. End of dialog window.      Benni also received a warm welcome from City captain Lebogang Manyama on Wednesday. “Firstly, I would love to welcome Coach Benni. I think it’s very exciting obviously for the team to get a manager like Benni to lead us, because I think he is a person that has so much knowledge about football to share,” the skipper said via City’s Twitter account. “I’m very happy that we are going to be the team to benefit from that. It’s not going to be easy, but one thing I can assure him is that we are all in it with him all the way. Welcome to the CTCFC family, Coach Benni. All the best.” @ashfakmohamed IOL Sport   Like us on Facebook   Follow us on Twitter 